+++ b/docs/api/structures/focused-editable-text-options.md
@@ -4,9 +4,22 @@
   `surrounding`, or `full`. Default is `full`.
 * `maxLength` number (optional) - Maximum number of UTF-16 code units to return
   in `text`. Must be between `1` and `1000000`. Default is `100000`.
+* `includeHtml` boolean (optional) - Whether to include the focused
+  contenteditable host's raw `innerHTML` in `html`. Only valid when `mode` is
+  `full`, or when `mode` is omitted because `full` is the default. Default is
+  `false`.
+* `maxHtmlLength` number (optional) - Maximum number of UTF-16 code units to
+  return in `html` when `includeHtml` is `true`. Only valid when `mode` is
+  `full`, or when `mode` is omitted because `full` is the default. Must be
+  between `1` and `1000000`. Default is `100000`.
 
 When `mode` is `value`, Electron reads Chromium's current focused input value
 snapshot when available. When `mode` is `surrounding`, Electron reads text
 around the current selection from Blink. When `mode` is `full`, Electron reads
 the full focused editable DOM text on a best-effort basis and truncates around
 the current selection if the text is longer than `maxLength`.
+
+For contenteditable and `designMode` editors, `full` uses a best-effort
+block-aware text serializer so elements such as `<p>`, `<div>`, and `<br>` are
+represented with line breaks in `text`. `html` is raw DOM `innerHTML` for the
+focused editable host; it is not sanitized or normalized.
