 # FocusedEditableTextWatchOptions Object
 
-Extends `FocusedEditableTextOptions`.
+Extends the mode-specific `FocusedEditableTextOptions` union with
+`throttleMs`. The watcher default `mode` is `surrounding`, so `includeHtml` and
+`maxHtmlLength` require `mode: 'full'` when used with this object.
 
 * `mode` string (optional) - The text range to read. Can be `value`,
   `surrounding`, or `full`. Default is `surrounding`.
 * `maxLength` number (optional) - Maximum number of UTF-16 code units to return
   in `text`. Must be between `1` and `1000000`. Default is `100000`.
+* `includeHtml` boolean (optional) - Whether to include the focused
+  contenteditable host's raw `innerHTML` in `html`. Only valid when `mode` is
+  `full`. Default is `false`.
+* `maxHtmlLength` number (optional) - Maximum number of UTF-16 code units to
+  return in `html` when `includeHtml` is `true`. Only valid when `mode` is
+  `full`. Must be between `1` and `1000000`. Default is `100000`.
 * `throttleMs` number (optional) - Minimum interval between callback deliveries
   for a watcher, in milliseconds. Must be between `0` and `60000`. Default is
   `50`.
