+++ b/docs/api/web-contents.md
@@ -1271,6 +1271,12 @@ canvas, virtual documents, or application-internal models may only expose the
 focused DOM control. Empty text controls resolve with `text: ''` rather than
 `null`.
 
+For contenteditable editors whose visual paragraphs are represented by DOM
+structure rather than literal newline text nodes, `full` mode returns a
+best-effort block-aware text snapshot. Pass `includeHtml: true` to include the
+focused editable host's raw `innerHTML` in `html`. `includeHtml` and
+`maxHtmlLength` are only valid with `full` mode.
+
 #### `contents.watchFocusedEditableText([options, ]callback)` _Experimental_
 
 * `options` [FocusedEditableTextWatchOptions](structures/focused-editable-text-watch-options.md) (optional)
@@ -1288,6 +1294,9 @@ watcher is created, and then again when Electron observes input state, caret,
 selection, composition, or focus changes that may affect the focused editable
 text snapshot.
 
+When using `includeHtml` or `maxHtmlLength` with a watcher, pass
+`mode: 'full'` explicitly. The watcher default mode is `surrounding`.
+
 Each watcher owns its own `options`, so multiple callers can watch the same
 WebContents with different `mode`, `maxLength`, or `throttleMs` values without
 overwriting each other. Call
